category or the other.

24
00:03:20,537 --> 00:03:23,637
Even those in innocent years
of elementary school, one

25
00:03:23,670 --> 00:03:25,637
could not escape that fact.

26
00:03:25,670 --> 00:03:28,370
As class president, I strived
to achieve great things

27
00:03:28,404 --> 00:03:32,137
for my fellow students, but
there were always enemies.

28
00:03:32,170 --> 00:03:33,370
Good against evil.

29
00:03:36,070 --> 00:03:36,537
-No!

30
00:03:36,570 --> 00:03:37,237
Stop!

31
00:03:37,270 --> 00:03:38,470
Let go of me, please!

32
00:03:40,804 --> 00:03:42,670
MIKAMI (VOICEOVER): Evil
has to be confronted.

33
00:03:42,704 --> 00:03:43,937
-What do you want, nerd?

34
00:03:46,804 --> 00:03:48,270
MIKAMI (VOICEOVER):
There were times

35
00:03:48,304 --> 00:03:52,104
when it seemed evil
would triumph over good.

36
00:03:52,137 --> 00:03:54,070
But no matter what
happened to me,

37
00:03:54,104 --> 00:03:56,904
I felt happy for one reason.

38
00:03:56,937 --> 00:04:00,170
-Thank you, Teru.

39
00:04:00,204 --> 00:04:02,337
MIKAMI (VOICEOVER): Hearing
those words of gratitude

40
00:04:02,370 --> 00:04:06,737
from the victims made me want
to save them again and again.

41
00:04:06,770 --> 00:04:10,270
For that reason, I
never spared any effort.

42
00:04:10,304 --> 00:04:13,937
And in the end, I
was able to stand up

43
00:04:13,970 --> 00:04:17,237
for my sense of justice.

44
00:04:17,270 --> 00:04:19,604
[snickering]

45
00:04:19,637 --> 00:04:21,104
-Does this bug you?

46
00:04:30,104 --> 00:04:32,004
MIKAMI (VOICEOVER):
But that was only true

47
00:04:32,037 --> 00:04:33,037
in the world of children.

48
00:04:38,637 --> 00:04:42,070
Middle school was
another matter entirely.

49
00:04:42,104 --> 00:04:46,004
The more I confronted evil,
the more enemies I had to face.

50
00:04:48,804 --> 00:04:50,537
Victims would
become participants,

51
00:04:50,570 --> 00:04:53,504
and even the people watching
would be influenced by evil

52
00:04:53,537 --> 00:04:55,070
and become enemies themselves.

53
00:04:58,737 --> 00:05:02,604
But for justice to triumph,
it requires action.

54
00:05:02,637 --> 00:05:07,804
So I realized, to serve
justice, I had to delete evil.

55
00:05:07,837 --> 00:05:11,737
The only person who understood
my hopes and remained my ally

56
00:05:11,770 --> 00:05:14,537
was the woman who
raised me on her own.

57
00:05:14,570 --> 00:05:16,504
My mother.

58
00:05:16,537 --> 00:05:17,404
No.

59
00:05:17,437 --> 00:05:19,704
Rather, it used to be my mother.

60
00:05:23,170 --> 00:05:25,304
WOMAN: Teru, not
everything in the world

61
00:05:25,337 --> 00:05:28,404
is going to work the
way you want it to.

62
00:05:28,437 --> 00:05:29,904
You have to stop doing this.

63
00:05:29,937 --> 00:05:31,370
There's no reason
for you to suffer

64
00:05:31,404 --> 00:05:32,870
so much for your beliefs.

65
00:05:32,904 --> 00:05:36,404
What do you think you're
proving getting hurt like this?

66
00:05:36,437 --> 00:05:38,304
This is plain foolishness.

67
00:05:38,337 --> 00:05:40,304
You have to do

68
00:05:40,337 --> 00:05:41,970
MIKAMI (VOICEOVER):
My mother was wrong.

69
00:05:42,004 --> 00:05:45,237
She didn't side with justice.

70
00:05:45,270 --> 00:05:49,137
She was one of those who
deserved to be deleted.

71
00:05:49,170 --> 00:05:51,070
That was when the
miracle happened.

72
00:05:54,004 --> 00:05:56,570
Four of the worst
delinquents from my school

73
00:05:56,604 --> 00:05:59,637
lost control of their car
while they were joyriding.

74
00:05:59,670 --> 00:06:01,037
They died instantly.

75
00:06:01,070 --> 00:06:03,570
One bystander was
killed as well.

76
00:06:03,604 --> 00:06:07,604
That bystander was my mother.

77
00:06:07,637 --> 00:06:10,104
In one fell swoop, all
the people I resented

78
00:06:10,137 --> 00:06:11,970
had been deleted.

79
00:06:12,004 --> 00:06:14,404
At first, I was terrified.

80
00:06:14,437 --> 00:06:17,004
I couldn't stop shivering.

81
00:06:17,037 --> 00:06:19,437
But then it hit me.

82
00:06:19,470 --> 00:06:21,304
With these people
out of the picture,

83
00:06:21,337 --> 00:06:24,070
how many others would
benefit as a result?

84
00:06:24,104 --> 00:06:26,570
Clearly their victims
were relieved.

85
00:06:26,604 --> 00:06:27,937
But beyond that.

86
00:06:27,970 --> 00:06:29,770
Would'nt everyone in my class
be happier now that they were

87
00:06:29,804 --> 00:06:32,004
gone?

88
00:06:32,037 --> 00:06:34,137
And sure enough, I was right.

89
00:06:34,170 --> 00:06:36,370
Our classroom became a
peaceful, joyful place.

90
00:06:39,304 --> 00:06:42,204
There will always
consequences f evil deeds.

91
00:06:42,237 --> 00:06:44,404
That is the way the world is.

92
00:06:44,437 --> 00:06:45,304
The way it should be.

93
00:06:48,037 --> 00:06:51,704
Evil must be deleted.

94
00:06:51,737 --> 00:06:53,670
Now then, let's see.

95
00:06:53,704 --> 00:06:55,804
Are there any more problems
with these records?

96
00:06:55,837 --> 00:06:56,937
-No, they're fine.

97
00:06:56,970 --> 00:06:58,404
MIKAMI (VOICEOVER):
With every passing year,

98
00:06:58,437 --> 00:07:01,037
my commitment to justice
only grew stronger.

99
00:07:01,070 --> 00:07:02,937
I saw that there
will always be those

100
00:07:02,970 --> 00:07:05,270
who have no reason to exist.

101
00:07:05,304 --> 00:07:09,337
Those whose very existence
is a threat to society.

102
00:07:09,370 --> 00:07:12,370
And the closer they grew to
adulthood, the less likely

103
00:07:12,404 --> 00:07:15,004
was that they would ever reform.

104
00:07:15,037 --> 00:07:16,504
They could only be deleted.

105
00:07:22,370 --> 00:07:25,670
Mysteriously, every time
I judged someone as evil,

106
00:07:25,704 --> 00:07:28,670
they would soon
be taken care of.

107
00:07:28,704 --> 00:07:30,170
Was it coincidence?

108
00:07:30,204 --> 00:07:32,270
Was I special somehow?

109
00:07:32,304 --> 00:07:35,304
In the end, it didn't matter.

110
00:07:35,337 --> 00:07:38,070
Divine judgment must
be brought up evil.

111
00:07:38,104 --> 00:07:41,237
And if it isn't, then someone
must take it upon themselves

112
00:07:41,270 --> 00:07:43,904
to punish evil.

113
00:07:43,937 --> 00:07:46,137
That's why I became
a prosecutor.

114
00:07:46,170 --> 00:07:48,037
It is the role of
the prosecutor to see

115
00:07:48,070 --> 00:07:49,970
that evil is brought to justice.

116
00:07:50,004 --> 00:07:53,570
It was an ideal job for me.

117
00:07:53,604 --> 00:07:58,804
And then God came before me.

118
00:07:58,837 --> 00:08:01,104
Everything that had
been happening around me

119
00:08:01,137 --> 00:08:03,104
wasn't coincidence.

120
00:08:03,137 --> 00:08:04,804
It was divine justice.

121
00:08:07,470 --> 00:08:09,504
God had been watching me.

122
00:08:12,670 --> 00:08:15,870
God had seen how I did
not surrender to evil.

123
00:08:15,904 --> 00:08:17,770
He reached out his
hand and punished

124
00:08:17,804 --> 00:08:20,004
the evil people for me.

125
00:08:20,037 --> 00:08:22,704
Once I realized that, I
started to frequent places

126
00:08:22,737 --> 00:08:24,904
where God was bound
to be watching.

127
00:08:24,937 --> 00:08:25,770
And then it happened.

128
00:08:31,404 --> 00:08:34,837
God recognized me as
I had always hoped!

129
00:08:34,870 --> 00:08:37,704
Not only that, but he found
me worthy of sharing his power

130
00:08:37,737 --> 00:08:38,804
to eliminate evil!

131
00:08:42,904 --> 00:08:45,870
With this, it doesn't matter
if I can't hear his voice.

132
00:08:45,904 --> 00:08:50,437
I shall figure out what Kira
wants and carry out his will.

