00:09:20,516 --> 00:09:22,183
LIGHT (VOICEOVER):
Mikami made the choice

145
00:09:22,216 --> 00:09:24,083
to kill Demegawa himself.

146
00:09:24,116 --> 00:09:25,550
I never requested it.

147
00:09:25,583 --> 00:09:28,483
An understandable move, but
now there's no spokesperson.

148
00:09:28,516 --> 00:09:30,383
Kira needs a voice.

149
00:09:30,416 --> 00:09:33,516
At the moment, I can't
make any moves myself.

150
00:09:33,550 --> 00:09:35,216
What will he do?

151
00:09:35,250 --> 00:09:37,283
-Kira isn't saying anything.

152
00:09:37,316 --> 00:09:40,816
He must be in a situation
where he can't move freely.

153
00:09:40,850 --> 00:09:42,883
But this is an
important time for him.

154
00:09:42,916 --> 00:09:46,550
We need a spokesperson to
spread his word to the people.

155
00:09:46,583 --> 00:09:47,883
Then I will take the initiative.

156
00:09:50,850 --> 00:09:52,350
-Extra, extra!

157
00:09:52,383 --> 00:09:54,416
There's a new development
in the Kira case.

158
00:09:54,450 --> 00:09:57,616
He's chosen a new spokesperson
to take Demegawa's place.

159
00:09:57,650 --> 00:09:58,150
Take a look.

160
00:10:02,483 --> 00:10:03,716
LIGHT (VOICEOVER): That woman.

161
00:10:07,383 --> 00:10:09,616
Kiyomi Takada

162
00:10:09,650 --> 00:10:11,450
-Good evening.

163
00:10:11,483 --> 00:10:13,550
This is Kiyomi
Takada from News 6.

164
00:10:13,583 --> 00:10:16,650
Starting today, it will be my
duty to spread the word of Kira

165
00:10:16,683 --> 00:10:17,983
accurately and quickly.

166
00:10:18,016 --> 00:10:19,716
From now on, NHN will fairly--

167
00:10:19,750 --> 00:10:23,383
MATSUDA: So he picked
NHN's star newscaster, huh?

168
00:10:23,416 --> 00:10:24,650
Kira's got good taste.

169
00:10:24,683 --> 00:10:28,283
Choosing Taki was a good idea.

170
00:10:28,316 --> 00:10:29,816
-(VOICEOVER) There's
no mistaking it.

171
00:10:29,850 --> 00:10:32,016
That's the girl that
Light dated in university.

172
00:10:32,050 --> 00:10:34,516
KIYOMI: --but also his liaison
with the people of the world.

173
00:10:34,550 --> 00:10:36,450
-You've moved quickly, Mikami.

174
00:10:36,483 --> 00:10:38,150
However, it won't
take them long to find

175
00:10:38,183 --> 00:10:41,283
the connection between us,
which could be a problem.

176
00:10:41,316 --> 00:10:42,350
No.

177
00:10:42,383 --> 00:10:44,083
On second thought,
she's not a bad choice.

178
00:10:44,116 --> 00:10:46,383
It's one I never would have
considered, since I already

179
00:10:46,416 --> 00:10:47,483
knew her.

180
00:10:47,516 --> 00:10:49,716
But this could actually
make things easier.

181
00:10:49,750 --> 00:10:51,483
I can definitely
use her, but I'll

182
00:10:51,516 --> 00:10:54,683
have to find a way
to contact her soon.

183
00:10:54,716 --> 00:10:55,783
(VOICEOVER) Kiyomi Takada.

184
00:10:57,250 --> 00:10:59,716
I had a chance to meet her when
I was part of a debate program

185
00:10:59,750 --> 00:11:01,183
she was hosting.

186
00:11:01,216 --> 00:11:04,016
She was a shrewd and fair
host for the most part,

187
00:11:04,050 --> 00:11:05,483
but her attitude
changed suddenly

188
00:11:05,516 --> 00:11:07,216
when Kira's name was mentioned.

189
00:11:07,250 --> 00:11:09,683
She had a uniquely
rigid sense of justice

190
00:11:09,716 --> 00:11:11,450
that I could identify with.

191
00:11:11,483 --> 00:11:14,816
She hates crimes and social
evils with a passion.

192
00:11:14,850 --> 00:11:17,650
I talked with her privately
several times after that.

193
00:11:17,683 --> 00:11:19,483
She clearly supports Kira.

194
00:11:19,516 --> 00:11:21,450
But it's more than that.

195
00:11:21,483 --> 00:11:23,583
She thinks like Kira.

196
00:11:23,616 --> 00:11:25,650
That makes her the
broadcaster most worthy

197
00:11:25,683 --> 00:11:28,216
of being the new voice of Kira.

198
00:11:33,716 --> 00:11:35,283
-(VOICEOVER) Kiyomi Takada.

199
00:11:35,316 --> 00:11:36,950
It'd to be too
suspicious for Kira

200
00:11:36,983 --> 00:11:39,483
to choose an ex-girlfriend
as his representative.

201
00:11:39,516 --> 00:11:43,216
And there's been no sign of
Light sending her any messages.

202
00:11:43,250 --> 00:11:46,883
Maybe I'm thinking
about this too much.

203
00:11:46,916 --> 00:11:49,750
-Everyone, I just had an idea.

204
00:11:49,783 --> 00:11:52,983
I was thinking we could
make use of Kiyomi Takada.

205
00:11:53,016 --> 00:11:54,683
To be honest, I know her.

206
00:11:54,716 --> 00:11:56,883
Back in university,
she and I were actually

207
00:11:56,916 --> 00:11:58,316
dating for a little while.

208
00:11:58,350 --> 00:11:59,183
-Whoa.

209
00:11:59,216 --> 00:12:00,450
-(VOICEOVER) So he admits it.

210
00:12:00,483 --> 00:12:02,950
He has no intention to
hide the connection.

211
00:12:02,983 --> 00:12:04,883
-If she's acting as
his spokesperson,

212
00:12:04,916 --> 00:12:07,283
she must be receiving
orders from him.

213
00:12:07,316 --> 00:12:09,283
She's in contact
with Kira somehow.

214
00:12:09,316 --> 00:12:11,216
I think our best bet is
to use that connection

215
00:12:11,250 --> 00:12:12,883
to find a way to
Kira through her.

216
00:12:12,916 --> 00:12:13,916
[growl]

217
00:12:13,950 --> 00:12:15,083
MATSUDA: But Taki's
probably doing it

218
00:12:15,116 --> 00:12:16,783
because Kira's
threatening her, right?

219
00:12:16,816 --> 00:12:19,816
She might be too scared to help
us out with her investigation.

220
00:12:19,850 --> 00:12:21,350
IDE: That's a good point.

221
00:12:21,383 --> 00:12:23,283
-I'm not too worried about that.

222
00:12:23,316 --> 00:12:24,916
I know her current
cell phone number.

223
00:12:24,950 --> 00:12:26,983
I'm pretty sure that I'll
be able to convince her

224
00:12:27,016 --> 00:12:27,950
once we get talking.

225
00:12:27,983 --> 00:12:30,116
She'll meet with
me if I ask her to.

226
00:12:30,150 --> 00:12:30,883
-Ha ha.

227
00:12:30,916 --> 00:12:31,650
Wow.

228
00:12:31,683 --> 00:12:32,916
Listen to this guy.

229
00:12:32,950 --> 00:12:34,450
You're the man, Light.

230
00:12:34,483 --> 00:12:36,650
-Talking to her will be
easy, but the real challenge

231
00:12:36,683 --> 00:12:39,550
will be to get her to help
us find and arrest Kira.

232
00:12:39,583 --> 00:12:41,483
We used to talk about a
lot of different topics

233
00:12:41,516 --> 00:12:44,883
while we were in college,
and one thing was clear.

234
00:12:44,916 --> 00:12:47,250
She worships Kira.

235
00:12:47,283 --> 00:12:52,183
But we might be able to
use that to our advantage.

236
00:12:52,216 --> 00:12:54,850
The police claim they
support Kira, but aren't

237
00:12:54,883 --> 00:12:56,883
doing anything one
way or the other.

238
00:12:56,916 --> 00:12:58,683
So I'll reveal that
I've joined the police,

239
00:12:58,716 --> 00:13:01,250
and ask her what we can
do to help Kira further.

240
00:13:01,283 --> 00:13:04,450
To her, it'll sound
like a good idea.

241
00:13:04,483 --> 00:13:06,516
We can convince her to
assist us as long as we

242
00:13:06,550 --> 00:13:09,250
pretend it's for Kira's benefit.

243
00:13:09,283 --> 00:13:11,116
-Do you think
that'll go over well?

244
00:13:11,150 --> 00:13:12,350
-I'm not entirely sure.

245
00:13:12,383 --> 00:13:13,950
But it's worth a try, at least.

246
00:13:13,983 --> 00:13:15,216
-I agree.

247
00:13:15,250 --> 00:13:18,350
It'd be foolish for us to
pass up a lead like this.

248
00:13:18,383 --> 00:13:20,050
-In that case, I'll
call her tonight.

249
00:13:20,083 --> 00:13:21,650
AIZAWA: Light.

250
00:13:21,683 --> 00:13:23,216
If you don't mind,
I'd like to listen

251
00:13:23,250 --> 00:13:24,883
in on your conversation
with Ms. Takada.

252
00:13:24,916 --> 00:13:26,116
-Of course.

253
00:13:26,150 --> 00:13:27,516
That's fine with me.

254
00:13:27,550 --> 00:13:29,183
Actually, it's better if you do.

255
00:13:29,216 --> 00:13:30,750
If she lets slip
something about Kira,

256
00:13:30,783 --> 00:13:33,750
it would be best if more
than one of us was listening.

257
00:13:33,783 --> 00:13:35,183
-Uh-- yeah.

258
00:13:40,716 --> 00:13:43,850
[phone ringing]

259
00:13:43,883 --> 00:13:44,950
-Yes, Hello?

260
00:13:44,983 --> 00:13:45,650
